  <prompt>
    Update the `ISendEmailDialogProps` interface (exported from `@spaarke/ui-components`) to the canonical signature defined by FR-03 + FR-14. Remove the legacy `onSend` callback. Final shape:

    ```typescript
    export interface ISendEmailDialogProps {
      open: boolean;
      onClose: () => void;
      initialTo?: string | string[];
      initialSubject?: string;
      associations?: CommunicationAssociation[];
      attachmentSources?: AttachmentSourceKind[];
      onSent?: (communicationId: string) => void;
      onError?: (error: SendCommunicationError) => void;
    }
    ```

    The interface MUST live colocated with the canonical wrapper (most likely `EmailComposer/wrappers/SendEmailDialog.tsx` or its `index.ts`) and be re-exported from the top-level `@spaarke/ui-components` barrel.

    This is interface-only — no implementation logic changes here. Task 050 already integrated the canonical wrapper into the production export path; this task locks the type contract that consumers (task 051, task 053) migrate against.

    DO NOT remove the legacy `onSend` field gradually — REMOVE it entirely. The break-and-migrate forcing function is the desired behavior per spec FR-14 (every consumer must explicitly switch to the new contract). After this task, TypeScript will not compile any consumer still using `onSend` — that compilation failure surfaces the audit list for task 053.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    TypeScript developer authoritative on `@spaarke/ui-components` public type contracts. Familiar with the canonical wrapper signature per FR-03, the legacy `onSend` callback being deprecated, and the TypeScript-driven migration forcing function.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `ISendEmailDialogProps` exported from `@spaarke/ui-components` matches the canonical FR-03 + FR-14 signature: `{ open, onClose, initialTo?, initialSubject?, associations?, attachmentSources?, onSent?, onError? }`. Legacy `onSend` field REMOVED. `@spaarke/ui-components` builds clean (the interface change is self-contained). Downstream consumers (FilePreviewDialog and any others surfaced by task 053) will fail TypeScript compilation until migrated — this is the desired forcing function.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Pre-R3 `ISendEmailDialogProps` exposed a legacy `onSend` callback that consumers populated with the request body for the dialog to invoke. R3 inverts this: the wrapper OWNS the send, parents react via `onSent` / `onError`. Task 050 integrates the canonical wrapper; THIS task locks the type contract.

      The interface lives either:
      (a) Colocated with the canonical wrapper at `EmailComposer/wrappers/SendEmailDialog.tsx`, or
      (b) In a dedicated types file under `EmailComposer/types.ts`.

      Either location is acceptable. Task 050 likely produced (a) — verify and adjust here if (b) is cleaner.

      Empirical state: a separate `SendEmailDialog/` directory existed pre-R3 with its own legacy `ISendEmailDialogProps`. Task 050 either rewrites that file or re-exports from the canonical wrapper. THIS task ensures the canonical interface is THE only definition; any duplicate legacy interface in `SendEmailDialog/` must be deleted.
    </background>
